Really sad they closed the kitchen for good, their food trucks are sometimes good, and they sell crawfish when it’s in season but I’ll always miss their poutine and German wurst sausage. They have a really good beer variety, they have less variety on tap than they used to, but their canned variety keeps growing. They’ve even added ciders which is something that’s seriously lacking in lafayette. On top of that most of the bartenders know the beer/ciders and can help you pick out something you’ll like to drink.

If you want to enjoy a piece of acadiana soul you need to visit. The area itself has old historical meaning so it's nice to see the life come back into it.

One of the gems of the new downtown. A beautiful, dog and family friendly patio space with a constantly changing, well-curated tap selection that always features standout local brews. The food on offer is well done, hearty drinkers' fare. The menu is limited, and absolutely lacks vegetarian-friendly options. Keep an eye on the permanent vendors' stalls in the back, reportedly to be the site of a weekly art market.
